    "completed": "False",
    "instruction": "Filter error_logs.csv for rows whose timestamp is within 2021-03-07 16:00:00+08:00 to 2021-03-07 16:30:00+08:00. Convert timestamps to ts_utc8 for display. Return:\n1) total number of error_log rows in the window;\n2) counts per cmdb_id (top 20) sorted by count desc;\n3) the earliest up to 20 rows in the window with columns: ts_utc8, cmdb_id, message.\nAlso, from log.csv within the same time window, extract rows for these components: Tomcat04, IG02, apache01, apache02, Tomcat01. For those rows join each with its global P95 (precomputed in log_agg_full) by (cmdb_id, log_name), flag anomalies where value >= p95, compute severity = value / p95, and return a compact anomaly summary aggregated by (cmdb_id, log_name) with columns: cmdb_id, log_name, anomaly_count, earliest_anomaly_ts_utc8, max_severity (limit top 20 sorted by max_severity desc). Keep full filtered tables in kernel variables but only print the compact outputs described above."
